1. Background

In our web project testing, one routine is to verify if the web page can display some special characters well.

So how many special characters are there need to be verified?

2. Special Characters

Below is an image version of the above table, in case some characters can not be displayed well:

The Alt code is for typing reference. You can type these characters by (From http://www.tedmontgomery.com/tutorial/altchrc.html)

1) Make sure Num Lock key has been pressed to activate the numeric key section of the keyboard.

2) Depress the Alt key.

3) While the Alt key is depressed, type the proper sequence of numbers (on the numeric keypad) of the ALT code from the table above.

4) Release the Alt key, and the character will appear.

Note: On a laptop computer, there usually is no numeric keypad. So, instead, depress the Fn (function) key, then the Alt key, then the numerical code sequence. The numbers are on the front of certain keyboard keys: M = 0, J = 1, K = 2, L = 3, U = 4, I = 5, O = 6, 7 = 7, 8 = 8, and 9 = 9.

3. Summary
